## Phase 0 - Box base packages

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y \
  git curl ripgrep fd-find bat tmux mosh xclip restic

# bun (Nick's standard - never npm)
curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash      # → ~/.bun/bin/bun

# Claude Code CLI
curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash   # or: bun add -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
```

Note `fd-find` installs as `fdfind` on Debian/Ubuntu and `bat` as `batcat`; symlink them to `fd`/`bat` to match Nick's muscle memory:
```bash
mkdir -p ~/.local/bin
ln -sf $(which fdfind) ~/.local/bin/fd
ln -sf $(which batcat) ~/.local/bin/bat
```

