## Phase 2 - The `rc` command

On the **Mac** (`~/.zshrc`) and any other client:

```bash
# rc = remote claude: durable mosh+tmux window onto the box
rc() {
  mosh box -- tmux new-session -A -s pai -c "$HOME/.claude"
}
# variant that boots straight into claude (auto-restarts the pane if claude exits)
rcc() {
  mosh box -- tmux new-session -A -s pai -c "$HOME/.claude" \
    'while true; do claude; echo "claude exited - enter to relaunch, ctrl-c to drop to shell"; read; done'
}
```

`tmux new-session -A -s pai` attaches if `pai` exists, creates it otherwise - so `rc` is idempotent and you always land in the same session. On the phone, the equivalent is a Blink host entry that runs `tmux new -A -s pai`.

Detach without killing: `Ctrl-b d`. The session (and any running agent) keeps going on the box.

