## Phase 5 - macOS-ism patches

The scan flagged these as the files with Darwin-only calls. The cadence runner and `Inference.ts` are clean and need nothing. The rest split into "patch" and "disable":

| File | Issue | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| `Pulse/start-pulse.sh`, `Pulse/manage.sh` | `launchctl`, `/opt/homebrew`, `stat -f` | Patch: `systemctl --user`, `$HOME/.bun`, `stat -c`. Add a `--linux` branch or fork the script. |
| `Pulse/VoiceServer/voice.ts` | `afplay`/`say` playback | Disable on the box. No speakers, no point. Route voice to Mac later if wanted. |
| `Pulse/lib/imessage-send.ts` | `osascript` iMessage | Disable. Mac-only API. Telegram covers outbound. |
| `Pulse/MenuBar/install.sh` | macOS menubar app | Skip entirely. |
| `statusline-command.sh` | `/opt/homebrew`, BSD `stat` | Patch only if you want the statusline over `rc`; low priority. |
| `Pulse/lib.ts` | likely `open`/`pbcopy` paths | Patch as encountered: `open`→`xdg-open`, `pbcopy`→`xclip -selection clipboard`. |

General sed rule when you hit them: BSD `stat -f` → GNU `stat -c`, `sed -i ''` → `sed -i`, `open` → `xdg-open`. Voice notifications: on a headless box the ElevenLabs API call still succeeds but plays into the void - either silence it (drop the playback step) or, later, have the box POST the audio to the Mac's Pulse for playback. Silence is the right default to start.

